Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?blueprint:=20incremental=20warm-rebuild=20engin?=
 =?UTF-8?q?e=20=E2=80=94=20O(edit)=20analysis=20+=20write,=20warm=20add?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Content-addressed incremental analysis on a resident graph (baselines,
DiffParsedModules, scoped re-mutation, provider-interface propagation) plus an
O(edit) ninja write.

This revision makes add-module warm and byte-identical, and the write O(edit)
across a membership change:
  - ChangedBlueprintFiles: reparse only the .bp files whose content hash changed
    (12 of 14,003 on a real edit; reparse ~4.4s -> ~0.4s);
  - shard the multi-GB incremental-modules subninja like the main modules;
  - shardModulesStable: content-addressed (hash-of-identity) shard assignment
    instead of position-based ShardByCount, so adding/removing a module leaves
    every other module in its shard -> delta write stays O(edit) on add (1 of 50
    shards rewritten, was 50/50);
  - reset each single-use singleton's generate-state before re-running on a
    membership change, so add no longer panics (provenance_metadata,
    all_aconfig_declarations) and produces byte-identical output.

All verified byte-identical to cold on real AOSP. Also includes incr/ (a separate
experimental native-emitter prototype). Local/experimental.

